  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">India Green Finance Initiative</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In 2020, Denmark and India formalized a Green Strategic Partnership Agreement. The purpose is to support India&#x2019;s green transition and strengthen Denmark&#x2019;s engagement in India. Under this agreement the Danish Minister for Development Cooperation has approved the India Green Investment Initiative, an earmarked capital contribution of DKK 200 million to the Investment Fund for Developing Countries (IFU). 

The objective is to target green investments in India related to renewable energy, energy efficiency, waste management, and water. This will contribute to the Danish government&apos;s target of ensuring that 30% of development assistance under &#xA7;6.3 of the finance act is green by 2023.</narrative>
  </description>
